ite for staff on Wednesday after claiming that a potential rescuer had enquired about buying all or some of the business.</p> <p>Mick Cash, the RMT’s general secretary, said: “Within the past 24 hours RMT has been made aware of what we believe to be a credible bid to take over some or all of the City Link trading operation.</p> <p>“At this stage we have no further details and we understand the matter is in the hands of the administrators with the government and [business secretary] Vince Cable aware of the situation. With today key in terms of redundancies RMT is urging the administrators to suspend the redundancy process and work with the government and the administrators to urgently evaluate and act on any viable options that could keep City Link trading as a going concern.”</p> <p>Administrators at Ernst &amp; Young (EY), who were formally appointed on Christmas Eve, have warned staff to expect “substantial redundancies” at the parcel firm’s depots around the country. A small number are expected to be retained to help deal with the estimated 30,000 parcels still being held at City Link’s depots, all of which are set to remain open until around 6 January.</p> <p>On Tuesday, the <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/dec/30/parcel-delivery-jobs-city-link-staff-apc-overnight\" title=\"\">courier company APC Overnight</a> said it would give priority to City Link staff in filling up to 100 vacancies at its national sorting centre in Cannock.</p> <p>The RMT has called on the business secretary, Vince Cable, to rescue the firm but Jon Moulton, the veteran private equity investor who heads City Link’s owner, Better Capital, has said the government was aware of the courier’s troubles before Christmas and did not request a meeting to discuss its future. He said the firm needed about £100m to turn itself around.</p> <p>Better Capital expects to <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/dec/29/city-link-private-equity-firm-hopes-recover-20m-despite-job-losses\" title=\"\">recover about £20m</a> from the failed company, but shares in the listed investment firm fell back this week as investors calculated that its losses would be greater than that.</p>","internalOctopusCode":"9934873","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-01-01T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","internalPageCode":"2216548","internalRevision":"18","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"More than 3,700 posts at risk as administrators warn of  ‘substantial redundancies’ at collapsed courier’s depots around UK","allowUgc":"false","headline":"City Link workers brace for redundancy notices despite rumours of potential buyer","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","byline":"Sarah Butler","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2014-12-31T08:19:33.577Z","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/12/31/1420013929775/5cc52636-6e07-41cd-9e17-7a6b534764e4-140x84.jpeg","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/44gea","wordcount":"390","shouldHideAdverts":"false","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/12/31/1420013929775/5cc52636-6e07-41cd-9e17-7a6b534764e4-140x84.jpeg","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"54a3b112e4b048dfa4053ac6","internalStoryPackageCode":"83826","commentCloseDate":"2015-01-03T08:19:34Z","standfirst":"More than 3,700 posts at risk as administrators warn of  ‘substantial redundancies’ at collapsed courier’s depots around UK","linkText":"City Link workers brace for redundancy notices despite rumours of potential buyer","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2015-01-06T11:03:42.000Z","internalContentCode":"454057573"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/dec/31/city-link-workers-brace-redundancy-notices","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/business/2014/dec/31/city-link-workers-brace-redundancy-notices","sectionName":"Business","elements":[{"id":"4c485fe4f2e11307eb6505f8c944e308fb85884d","relation":"main","type":"imag